    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The plane truss shown in the figure is subjected to an external force P. It is given that P = 70 kN, a = 2 m, and b = 3 m.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m1p6w5a5/85239244-040e-4950-b7f0-69ec1c5a97f6/2bf5d6d0-7f44-11ef-b740-5762ac8bb4a2/file-jaoe38c1m1p6w5a6.webp?format=webp\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m1p6w5a5/85239244-040e-4950-b7f0-69ec1c5a97f6/2bf5d6d0-7f44-11ef-b740-5762ac8bb4a2/file-jaoe38c1m1p6w5a6.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2022 Set 1 Structural Analysis - Truss Question 6 English\"></p>\n<p>The magnitude (absolute value) of force (in kN) in member EF is ________. (round off to the nearest integer)</p>",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "28TO32",
    "explanation": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m1p73ajy/2b62f147-34ac-46e1-af67-fa2d4cab0fe7/f2b274e0-7f44-11ef-b740-5762ac8bb4a2/file-jaoe38c1m1p73ajz.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m1p73ajy/2b62f147-34ac-46e1-af67-fa2d4cab0fe7/f2b274e0-7f44-11ef-b740-5762ac8bb4a2/file-jaoe38c1m1p73ajz.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2022 Set 1 Structural Analysis - Truss Question 6 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>$$\\Sigma$$M<sub>J</sub> = 0</p>\n<p>$$\\Rightarrow$$ V<sub>A</sub> $$\\times$$ 8 $$-$$ H<sub>A</sub> $$\\times$$ 1 $$-$$ 70 $$\\times$$ 4 = 0</p>\n<p>8V<sub>A</sub> $$-$$ H<sub>A</sub> = 280 ....... (i)</p>\n<p>To find H<sub>A</sub> (Cut the truss by 1 - 1)</p>\n<p>Consider left hand side</p>\n<p>$$\\Sigma$$M<sub>E</sub> = 0</p>\n<p>$$\\Rightarrow$$ V<sub>A</sub> $$\\times$$ 4 $$-$$ H<sub>A</sub> $$\\times$$ 4 = 0</p>\n<p>V<sub>A</sub> = H<sub>A</sub> ....... (ii)</p>\n<p>Using (i) in (ii) 8V<sub>A</sub> $$-$$ V<sub>A</sub> = 280</p>\n<p>7V<sub>A</sub> = 280</p>\n<p>V<sub>A</sub> = 40 kN</p>\n<p>H<sub>A</sub> = 40 kN</p>\n<p>$$\\Rightarrow$$ H<sub>J</sub> = 40 kN</p>\n<p>V<sub>J</sub> = 70 $$-$$ 40 = 30 kN</p>\n<p>To find force in member EF (Cut the truss by 2-2)</p>\n<p>Consider right hand side,</p>\n<p>Force in the member EF, F<sub>EF</sub> = V<sub>J</sub></p>\n<p>F<sub>EF</sub> = 30 kN</p>",
    "topic": null,
