    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The plane truss shown in the figure has 13 joints and 22 members. The truss is made of a homogeneous, prismatic, linearly elastic material. All members have identical axial rigidity. A to M indicate the joints of the truss. The truss has pin supports at joints A and L and roller support at joint K. The truss is subjected to a 10 kN vertically downward force at joint H and a 10 kN horizontal force in the rightward direction at joint B as shown.</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lxszgv82/6b6df286-deb1-4086-b9b5-8812cb9515b9/683b4f20-3229-11ef-b647-1f4d3dd537d9/file-jaoe38c1lxszgv83.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lxszgv82/6b6df286-deb1-4086-b9b5-8812cb9515b9/683b4f20-3229-11ef-b647-1f4d3dd537d9/file-jaoe38c1lxszgv83.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2024 Set 1 Structural Analysis - Truss Question 5 English\"><p>The magnitude of the reaction (in kN) at the pin support L is __________ (rounded off to 1 decimal place).</p>",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "7.0TO8.0",
    "explanation": null,
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "gate-ce-2024-set-1",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "direction": null,
    "comprehension": null,
    "content": "<p>Consider the pin-jointed truss shown in the figure (not to scale). All members have the same axial rigidity, AE. Members QR, RS, and ST have the same length L. Angles QBT, RCT, SDT are all 90°. Angles BQT, CRT, DST are all 30°. The joint T carries a vertical load P. The vertical deflection of joint T is k<span class=\"math-tex\">$\\rm \\frac{PL}{AE}$</span>. What is the value of k?</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzeo8umv/c2234560-9c74-4736-8361-615601aae677/fa8c9270-51e2-11ef-a345-ddfa5f530cc2/file-jaoe38c1lzeo8umw.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lzeo8umv/c2234560-9c74-4736-8361-615601aae677/fa8c9270-51e2-11ef-a345-ddfa5f530cc2/file-jaoe38c1lzeo8umw.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 1 Structural Analysis - Truss Question 3 English\">",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "1.5"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "4.5"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "3.0"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "9.0"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "explanation": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzeod30s/2a2e7b1f-b539-47b5-bf47-b55088d15ab7/70439cc0-51e3-11ef-a345-ddfa5f530cc2/file-jaoe38c1lzeod30t.png?format=png\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 1 Structural Analysis - Truss Question 3 English Explanation 1\">\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzeocxh0/b6d455c9-c390-4bf0-9506-fae85c2999e4/6bfa5a50-51e3-11ef-a345-ddfa5f530cc2/file-jaoe38c1lzeocxh1.png?format=png\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 1 Structural Analysis - Truss Question 3 English Explanation 2\">\n\n<p>Free Body Diagram of Joint T:</p>\n\n<p>\n\n</p><p>$$ \\Sigma M_B = 0, \\quad R \\times 3L \\sin 60^{\\circ} + P \\times 3L \\cos 60^{\\circ} = 0 $$</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>Considering joint T:</p>\n\n<p>\n\n</p><p>$$ \\begin{array}{ll} \\Sigma f_y = 0, &amp; F_{TQ} \\sin 60^{\\circ} = P, \\quad F_{TQ} = \\frac{2P}{\\sqrt{3}} = 1.1547 P \\\\\\\\ \\Sigma f_x = 0, &amp; F_{BT} = -F_{TQ} \\cos 60^{\\circ} = -0.577 P \\end{array} $$</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>Vertical deflection at joint T:</p>\n\n<p>\n\n</p><p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp;\\Delta V_T = \\sum \\frac{N_n L}{AE} = \\frac{(-0.577 P) \\times (-0.577) \\times 1.5L}{AE} + \\frac{(1.1547 P) \\times (1.1547) \\times 3L}{AE} = \\frac{4.5 PL}{AE} \\\\\\\\ &amp;\\therefore \\quad k = 4.5 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (B).</p>",
    "answer": null,
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "gate-ce-2023-set-1",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "direction": null,
    "comprehension": null,
    "content": "<p>An idealised bridge truss is shown in the figure. The force in Member U<span style=\" line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em;font-size:10.5px;\">2</span>L<span style=\" line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em;font-size:10.5px;\">3</span>&nbsp;is __________ kN (round off to one decimal place).</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzconuxk/faf3ccfe-a739-4fa3-8596-ebe53247699f/0a9ded80-50cb-11ef-a611-3fbeee6ccc16/file-jaoe38c1lzconuxl.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lzconuxk/faf3ccfe-a739-4fa3-8596-ebe53247699f/0a9ded80-50cb-11ef-a611-3fbeee6ccc16/file-jaoe38c1lzconuxl.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 1 Structural Analysis - Truss Question 2 English\">",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "explanation": "<p>The vertical reaction at the supports can be calculated using the symmetry of the structure :</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\text{Vertical reaction at supports} = \\frac{100}{2} = 50 \\text{kN} $$</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzcoqh00/2276df36-2570-4a7a-afe2-3c05204a174a/53483900-50cb-11ef-a611-3fbeee6ccc16/file-jaoe38c1lzcoqh01.png?format=png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 1 Structural Analysis - Truss Question 2 English Explanation 1\">\n\n<p>Next, by using the method of sections :</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzcosc4u/7ef076aa-92a4-4db0-872a-e1f2ec219a9c/872448e0-50cb-11ef-a611-3fbeee6ccc16/file-jaoe38c1lzcosc4v.png?format=png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 1 Structural Analysis - Truss Question 2 English Explanation 2\">\n\n<p>By summing up the vertical forces, we get :</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned}  &amp; \\sum V = 0 \\\\\\\\  &amp; F_{U_2L_3} \\cos 45^\\circ + 20 + 20 - 50 = 0 \\\\\\\\  &amp; F_{U_2L_3} = 10\\sqrt{2} = 14.14 \\text{kN} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct answer is 14.14 kN.</p>",
    "answer": "14.1",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "gate-ce-2023-set-1",
    "difficulty": null
  },
